  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for your feedback. We were sorry to learn that your experience was not as positive as we would hope on the Acute Medical Unit at Manchester Royal Infirmary. It is important to us that comments are heard and seen as an opportunity provided to the service to make changes and improvements wherever possible.

In response to your comment, we are reviewing our provision of pillows and will ensure that your concerns regarding staff attitude are also raised directly with the Unit Team so that others don't experience the same issues as you did.

It is difficult to respond to all posts in a full way often because of a breach of confidentiality particularly around the  decision to detain you therefore if you would like us to provide more detail around this, please do not hesitate to contact our Patient Advice and Liaison Service (PALS) on 0161 276 8686 or by e-mailing pals@mft.nhs.uk quoting reference number PO19/0061.

Kind regards,

Juliana McFarlane
Matron
Acute Medical Unit (AMU) and Ambulatory Care Unit (ACU)&lt;/CommentText&gt;
